    "honest_verdict": "PARTIAL FIX + a fundamental limit, honestly reported. CQR is the best distribution-free deployable method and delivers a real, statistically significant reduction of the conditional-coverage break, but it does not fully close it. The gap between the best deployable method (0.73) and the oracle ceiling (0.88) is an information limit of the committed near-constant base predictor, not a conformal-calibration failure. The honest operational conclusion: the trust gate should widen intervals via CQR AND flag the largest-effect stratum as residually under-covered until the base predictor carries effect-magnitude signal. No method fully closes the gap; we do not claim closure.",
